# Workflow — Self-Directed Execution

## Loop (every task)

1. **Plan** — Read `workflow_state.md`, relevant PRD sections, and touched modules. State goal + files in mind (briefly, internally).
2. **Execute** — Implement the smallest correct change. Prefer extending existing abstractions.
3. **Verify** — Run targeted tests, then broader suite if risk is high. Fix failures before declaring done.
4. **Improve** — Update `workflow_state.md`. Note follow-ups only if actionable.

## Autonomous continuation

- When **Current Task** is complete, take the next open **Backlog** item without asking.
- If Backlog is empty, add up to 5 actionable items from PRD/code gaps, then continue.
- See `.cursor/rules/autonomous-execution.mdc`.

## workflow_state.md (mandatory)

Path: **`d:/1jari/workflow_state.md`** (repo root).

Update at **start** (Current Task), **during** (Progress bullets), and **end** (Completed + Test/Lint status) of every session task.

Required sections:

```markdown
# Workflow State

## Current Task
- ...

## Backlog (priority order)
1. [ ] ...

## Definition of Done
- flutter analyze 0 errors; flutter test all pass; ...

## Progress
- [ ] ...
- [x] ...

## Completed (recent)
- YYYY-MM-DD — summary

## Blockers
- none | ...

## Verification
- Tests: ...
- Lint: ...
```

Keep **Completed (recent)** to the last ~10 entries. Archive old items into one-line summaries.

## When to delegate vs do directly

- Single coherent feature/bugfix: one end-to-end pass (investigate → code → test).
- Long builds or full test suites: run in background; fix failures when notified.
- Do not decompose small tasks into multiple agents.

## Interruptions

- Do not ask for permission to run tests, lint, or read-only exploration.
- Do ask before: production deploy, force git ops, committing secrets, deleting large data.

